            <c02 level="class">
               <did>
                  <unitid type="work">poems.elcc</unitid>
                  <unittitle type="uniform" label="Uniform Title:">
                     <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Elegy Written in a Country
							Churchyard</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unittitle label="First Line:">
                     <title linktype="simple">The curfew tolls the knell of parting day,</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate normal="1751" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1751</unitdate>
               </did>
               <bibliography>
                  <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                          linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966),  37-43</bibref>
                  <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#LoR_1969"
                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  103-141</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Begun <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1745"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="1745" certainty="circa" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">c. 1745</date>
                     </extref> and completed
							<extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1750"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="175006" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">early in June 1750</date>
                     </extref> at <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glplaces.shtml#Stoke Poges (Buckinghamshire, England, United         Kingdom), inhabited place [7011896]"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <geogname normal="Stoke Poges (Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom),          inhabited place [7011896]">Stoke Poges</geogname>
                     </extref>. 
							<persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771">Gray</persname> sent the poem
							in a <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0173"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">letter</extref> to
							<extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Walpole, Horace, 1717-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Walpole, Horace, 1717-1797">Horace
									Walpole</persname>
                     </extref> dated <date normal="17500612" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">12 June 1750</date>.
							First published, as <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1751"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">An Elegy wrote in a Country Church
									Yard</title>
                     </extref> and printed by <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Dodsley, Robert, 1703-1764"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Dodsley, Robert, 1703-1764">Dodsley</persname>
                     </extref>, in <date normal="1751" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1751</date>.
						</p>
               </scopecontent>
               <c03 level="item">
                  <did>
                     <unitid type="TGA">mss.0045</unitid>
                     <unitid type="work">poems.elcc</unitid>
                     <unittitle label="Title:">
                        <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Elegy, written in a Country-Church Yard.
									1750</title>
                     </unittitle>
                     <unitdate normal="1750" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1750</unitdate>
                     <physdesc>
                        <extent unit="pages">2</extent>
                        <physfacet>autograph, revised</physfacet>
                     </physdesc>
                     <physloc label="Identifier:">
                        <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Commonplace Book</title>, Vol. II,
								617-618 </physloc>
                     <physloc label="Building:"> College Library </physloc>
                     <repository>PBCC</repository>
                  </did>
                  <altformavail>
                     <p>Microfilm copy available in <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#MeP_1991"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poetic Commonplace Books and Manuscripts of Thomas Gray, 1716-1771, from Pembroke College, Cambridge</title> (1999),
								reel one</bibref>. Full facsimile published in <title render="italic" linktype="simple">A
									facsimile of the original autograph manuscript of Gray's Elegy</title>. 
								Photographed by Messrs. Cundall, Downes &amp; Co. London: Sampson Low,
								Son, &amp; Co. <date normal="1862" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862</date>, other facsimiles include <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#MaW_1814"
                                linktype="simple"> Mathias (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Works</title> (1814), vol. I, 	<extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;sequence=MaW_1814i:u6"
                                   show="replace"
                                   linktype="simple">following p.
										[64]</extref>
                        </bibref>, <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#P/W_1950"
                                linktype="simple"> Poole (ed.),
											<title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poetical Works</title> (1917), 
											90-91</bibref>, and Folger Shakespeare Library, ART Vol. a9, 
								follows p. 50.
							</p>
                  </altformavail>
                  <bibliography>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#SmM_1989"
                             linktype="simple">Smith (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Index</title> (1989), item GrT 34,  82</bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#MeP_1999"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poetic C.
								B.</title>, Pembroke College (1999),  27</bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#SuD_1995"
                             linktype="simple">Sutton (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Location Register</title> (1995),  414</bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                             linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966), additional
								stanza,  42n</bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#MnR_1931"
                             linktype="simple">Martin, <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Chronologie</title> (1931),  144</bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#NoC_1917"
                             linktype="simple">Northup, <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Bibliography</title> (1917), <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=secondary&amp;edition=NoC_1917&amp;page=250#bib1994"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">item	1994</extref>
                     </bibref>
                     <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#MaL_1976"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Elegy</title>
								(1976)</bibref>
                  </bibliography>
                  <scopecontent>
                     <p>Autograph, revised, here entitled <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Elegy, 
								written in a Country-Church Yard. 1750</title> and reading
								"Curfeu", with numbered lines (10, 20, etc.), an additional
								quatrain, the "Redbreast	stanza", annotated "Insert"
								after l. 116 and "Omitted in <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1753&amp;text=elcc"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <date normal="1753" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1753</date>
                        </extref>", and an extensive prose
								note, in <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771">Gray</persname>'s
								<title render="italic" linktype="simple">Commonplace Book</title>, vol. II, 
								617-618.
							</p>
                  </scopecontent>
